Process called "compile_and_run" that takes source as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Compile and run Runa source code
    Let compile_result be compile_source with source as source
    
    If not compile_result.success:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false and "error" as "Compilation failed: " plus compile_result.error
    
    Note: In a real implementation, this would execute the compiled bytecode
    Note: For now, we simulate successful execution
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true and "output" as "Simulated execution successful"

Process called "get_current_time_ms" returns Integer:
    Note: Get current time in milliseconds
    Return current_timestamp_ms

Note: Test Runner
Process called "main":
    Note: Main test runner
    Let result be run_runtime_integration_tests
    
    If result.success:
        Print "🎉 All Runtime Integration Tests PASSED!"
        Print "✅ Runtime works correctly with language keywords and standard library"
        Exit with code 0
    Otherwise:
        Print "💥 Some Runtime Integration Tests FAILED!"
        Print "❌ Runtime has issues with language keywords or standard library"
        Print "Failed tests: " plus result.failed_tests
        Exit with code 1 